sec.p:
In Sweden extensive care problems continuously have been described in the mass media and discussed by researchers during the last decades and especially after the reform, mentioned earlier on in this text, carried through in 1992 implying a radical ideological change of the care policy. By comparing the caregivers’ views and the care observed in three different cultures, one of the intentions with the study referred to in this article was to come closer to an understanding of those care problems reported. Based on these experiences, the primary aim of this article is to discuss the following questions:


The staff's view on the illness dementia;

The staff's view on older people suffering from dementia and the care provided;

The impact of the various views on the care delivered in relation to the care delivered and to the cultural context.
